
Overview of noun brink

The noun brink has 3 senses (first 1 from tagged texts)
                                          
1. (1) brink, threshold, verge -- (a region marking a boundary)
2. brink -- (the edge of a steep place)
3. verge, brink -- (the limit beyond which something happens or changes; "on the verge of tears"; "on the brink of bankruptcy")
